qas.question: What Iraqi leader clashed with Nasser?
What did Quasm do to anger Nasser?
What did Nasser suppress as a result?
What old ally did Nasser turn against?

context: Relations between Nasser and <a0_0>Qasim<a0_0/> grew increasingly bitter on 9 March, after Qasim's forces <a1_0>suppressed a rebellion in Mosul<a1_0/>, launched a day earlier by a pro-Nasser Iraqi RCC officer backed by UAR authorities. Nasser had considered dispatching troops to aid his Iraqi sympathizers, but decided against it. He clamped down on <a2_0>Egyptian communist activity<a2_0/> due to the key backing Iraqi communists provided Qasim. Several influential communists were arrested, including Nasser's old comrade <a3_0>Khaled Mohieddin<a3_0/>, who had been allowed to re-enter Egypt in 1956.
